rComments: Keegan was a very good teacher in so far that she was very enthusiastic about the texts she provided and discussed. Some might think that participating sucks but for writing classes the high level of participation required was just right! Take her class if you're really into writing and lit :)

I really liked Keegan in the beginning, but she began to get snippy and rude towards the end because she wanted students to participate and only a couple that knew what they were talking about would. The readings she assigns are so DRY...my entire class agreed that the reader was really boring. But she's decent and enjoys the subject.
